						               													<description>Imagine a cooperative exploration game in the tradition of Indiana Jones with a &amp;quot;lite&amp;quot; blend of a good ol' fashioned dungeon crawl using modular tiles and deadly traps.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It even has a light battle mechanic, so players can choose whether to work together or to betray their friends in their quest to escape alive with the master treasure chest. Players will take turns moving through the dungeon, building it as they go, and using up to 3 actions each turn. Traps spring up randomly, as do monsters... and glorious treasure. Treasure cards reveal bonuses to movement and combat. At any point a player may decide to attack another player and escape alone with the treasure, becoming the only winner at the table.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;And the best part is, all the mechanics work well either in large groups, small groups, or even solo.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It's a &amp;quot;lite&amp;quot; tabletop roleplaying game with a very basic dungeon crawl that can be done co-op, solo, or even versus.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
